                                                        <p>
                                                        <strong>Color-coding</strong> to add meaning just gives a visual cue, which users of assistive technologies like screen readers won't be able to understand. Make sure the informationÂ color designates is either evident from the content itself (such as the visible text) or is included in another way, such as by hiding additional text using the <code>.visually-hidden</code> class.
